reviews.review_text: Update: price has gone up at least 25-35% last month. Still reasonable I think Delicious!! Fish batter was thin, light and crunchy. Everything so fresh. 1 piece combo includes fries and soup for $7. $5.5 if you don t need soup. 2 pieces combo for $10 Cash only I believe
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much. Yes, the price is absolutely legendary. Please come back soon for more. Youve seen the small boss. God knows how much longer she can last doing it day in day out at her old age!

reviews.review_text: This place is amazing. Great prices and tasty fish and chips. The batter is light, crispy and sticks to the fish. Every bite of fish had a bite of crispy batter. The batter didn t fall off the fish like many places. Not to mention the fish was super moist. Chips were good and slaw was nice and tangy. What a nice meal to end the week !
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Wow! Fantastic review, thank you so much

reviews.review_text: Hidden gem for fish and chips. Great deal on high quality halibut. The fish is fresh, thick, moist inside with a crispy layer outside. House cut fries and homemade tartar sauce were amazing! Best part, they value providing high quality food such as using Canadian made vegetable oil as opposed to canola oil, which greatly impacted the flavour and didnt make the texture overly greasy. Friendly, respectful and kind service at this family run restaurant.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the awesome review!! Come back soon!

reviews.review_text: A great unassuming fish and chips place that my husband and I happened to come across. The interior is pretty basic and nothing to write home about, but the food was delicious and service quick. I got the halibut which was fried to perfection - crisp on the outside, juicy on the inside. The fries and coleslaw were also fantastic though I would ve liked a bit more slaw because it was so good. Husband got the regular fish (we re assuming cod) which was also delicious and cheaper than halibut. He got the chowder with his combo which lacked salt but was an easy fix and would be good for those trying to be mindful of their salt intake. We were the only customers for a while on a Tuesday at lunch so you wouldn t have to wait long if you re in a rush. We will definitely be back!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much, Mindy! Fantastic. Please come back for more soon!

reviews.review_text: I was super impressed by this place and almost cried for the quality and price. How can this be so cheap but tasty?? The combo is less than $7 and it includes fish, chips, seafood chowder soup, coleslaw, mayo sauce, ketchup. And one of the staff approached to me and asked how the food is. I can see that they are so caring of customers. Everything was great, but the greatest one was seafood soup. I was really craving for a cream soup, and I was fully satisfied with this soup. The French fries were ordinary though. The black coffee was instant one but it was only $1.5, so I liked it. I will visit again for sure !!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Vero Vero, thank you so much for your honest and heartfelt review. We are very humbled. We have been frying fish and chips the old way for almost three decades. Same price, same quality and same heart. Thank you and please come back soon. We are getting old and dont know how long we will last. One dish and one day at a time we go.

reviews.review_text: This place is not at all fancy, but it has the best fish and chips Ive found in Vancouver. The crust was beautiful and crispy, while the fish was perfectly cooked on the inside. Not at all over-cooked and dry. It was perfect.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: You are the best. Thank you, sir!!!!!

reviews.review_text: Stunned by the hospitality of the aged owner from Hong Kong, reminds me of those family-own chippy in London, UK (always forget there s London in Canada). The hand cut chips are sooo great and sadly no fresh halibut until summer. Batter is thin and just right. And they have malt vinegar! If there s HP sauce I would be more than delighted. Will definitely come back and chat with them.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Yes, sir, please come back soon for more!! You review is awesome!!

reviews.review_text: Cash only. Greeted at the door. A nice friendly family run restaurant. Double sided menu. Good sized portions. Great prices. Good location with parking lot. Fish is lightly battered, non oily or greasy. Back of the menu, I had 2 pieces of fish and chips. It came with a glass of water, individual dish of tartar sauce. The front of the menu 2 pieces of fish and chips with soup of the day or can of pop and coleslaw.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Great that you enjoyed your meal. Thank you.

reviews.review_text: Visited this place for the very first time last week( despite living in the neighborhood)and Ill have to agree this is the right place for me to enjoy a good lunch with friends or even all by myself ...fish is so crispy and only lightly battered... generous portion of french fries....plus the cole slaw is excellent also...Oh it comes with a bowl of clam chowder too ....all for a reasonable price of $14.95. For sure will come back more often!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Fantastic! Come back soon!

reviews.review_text: Exceedingly reason pieces, like a flash back to 15 years ago. Excellent quality of fish and shockingly fresh (I watched them bread and fry it infront of me). Go spend your money here!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for your appreciation. Awesome pics, too!!!

reviews.review_text: Excellent quality fish for far cheaper than anywhere else. I got the fish burger. On its own, it was rather plain, but I added a little dill ranch dressing and it was fantastic. Also, the fries needed salt, but just add salt yourself. The cokeslaw was better than pretty much everywhere I have gone. Where else are you going to get a good quality fish burger and fries for $8.50? Most places that I know are twice that price.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for the awesome review!!!!! Come back for more soon!

reviews.review_text: A great low key small local restaurant for my craving for fish and chips. Haha. They only take cash, but the amount and quality of food is phenomenal. One order of 2-piece fish and chips is only about $8. We had a full table of food for only $39. Lovely Cantonese speaking ladies always smile and say thanks. Will definitely come back.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! Please come back soon.

reviews.review_text: My neighbour recommended this restaurant. Price is excellent, fish was juicy. Fries, clam chowder and coleslaw were also good.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. Please come back for more soon!

reviews.review_text: Truly a hidden gem of a small fish and chips diner on Kingsway...Water, menu, condiments and ordering of the food were ready and available within minutes. The lunch combo fish was lightly battered and cooked to perfection! And to my delight, the senior woman owner came to greet us at the table and to ask in her Cantonese if everything was to our liking. Fortunately with my minimal Canadian Chinese, I said yes and thanked her as I would like to do the same in this review. To Seahouse Fish and Chips, thank you       for your service and the YUMMY fish combo.  Will definitely return and share this review with other diners. Kid-friendliness: Both younger and senior women owners are so hospitable that they will go out of their way to make their restaurant like your home. Wheelchair accessibility: Tables and chairs are flexible and light to move around in the large dining space.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Wow! Thank you for such a wonderful and thoughtful review. Come back soon, please!

reviews.review_text: The portions are small but so is the price, good value for the money. Very friendly and good, fast service. My wife and I got clam chowder and the 2 piece halibut and chips and coke to drink. I will go back again for sure. Parking: Parking lot is very small but there is free parking.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Fantastic! So happy you like the food. Come back for more soon.

reviews.review_text: Great fish and chips and well priced. They use basa and its soft and juicy. Family run with quick and friendly service. Wish I discovered this place earlier! Cash only Food
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much. Awesome!

reviews.review_text: Yummy fish and chips! The coleslaw is good too. The fried fish is fresh and lightly coated. We ordered the family set tonight and very delighted. Exceptional value when everything so expensive these days. Thank you for providing such yummy food with great value.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Fantastic! Glad your family enjoyed the meal. Come back for more soon!!!

reviews.review_text: Family run fish and chips shop.  Owner was nice and she prepared the order right after the order.  Ordered halibut and chips. The portion was decent size and quality was good.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Wow, cool! Thank you so much

reviews.review_text: Food was great. Not the commercial style fish and chips restaurant. Very home made which is wonderful.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Fantastic! Thank you very much

reviews.review_text: We decided to check out this place today as they got good reviews. I cannot imagine how I have never tried it before. We used to live about 4 blocks away and have never tried it. Anyway, they deserve the 5 stars for the food and of course the price. They only had the basa fish that day but it tasted really good. The batter was light and it was cooked well and not oily. The place is homey and looks like it is family owned. We will certainly come back and would like other folks to try their fish and chips as well. Parking: Enough parking spaces
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Yes, same family owned and operated for more than two decades! Come back for more soon! But price has to be adjusted soon because everything has gone up way too much!

reviews.review_text: Probably the best restaurant in Vancouver. Simple, no-frills and value. $5.50 for a hamburger with fries, cheapest in the city. You can t even get a quarter pounder at McDonalds for that price. The burger s patty is real beef, unlike McDonald s. The fish and fries are freshly fried right in front of you, and the batter is perfectly crispy and fresh is tender. The fries aren t salted, so make sure to salt them at home. I would love to try the halibut, but they ve been out the 3 times I ve been there. ~$30 for 10 pieces of fish + 3 fries, coleslaw, and gravy is such a good deal! Customer service is great, two or three Cantonese speaking aunties work there, they ve been running for 20-30 years. They tried to talk to my friend and I with our limited Cantonese/Mandarin skills. So nice!!! This place is a Vancouver hidden gem, standing strong in the face of inflation. I will be so sad if this place closes.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for your detailed review and recommendations. We really appreciate that. Unfortunately, due the high prices of everything we need to purchase to make our food nowadays, we have no choice but to increase our extremely low prices to a more moderate price point for all our menu items. Hope you come back again for more!

reviews.review_text: Stopped in for lunch today, they didnt have any halibut, so opted for the regular fish and chips. Fish was nice and thick, cooked perfectly with the proper amount of breading. Fries were a bit starchy, but the fish more than made up for it. Tartar sauce was quite tasty. The price is fantastic and the service was quite friendly. Will definitely be back. Parking: Parking is out front of the store.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Sorry, no halibut from Haida Gwaii for a while. Thank you for the fantastic review. Come back soon!!

reviews.review_text: My go to Fish and Chip place. Why? Still have 2 tables for dine in. They have really great lunch specials before 2 pm. Fantastic cod and halibut. A fish sandwich thats superb. Even great   burgers. The staff are super friendly, make sure your water   is always full.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: So nice to hear. Come back soon!

reviews.review_text: For the price this is unbeatable. Fish, fries and clam chowder soup for only $10!! The fish was just awesome to bite into and the chowder was great as well. Fries were only okay though but at this price you cant complain.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: You are right. What a deal! Come back soon for more!

reviews.review_text: The best and most affordable fish and chips in Vancouver. The fish portions are huge and always crispy. Love going here for a quick lunch.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. Please come back soon!!

reviews.review_text: Fish is  well seasoned and fried to perfection, tartar sauce is tangy and balances out the fish. Although prices have increased slightly, the quality is still the same, and I will continue to be a loyal customer! Thank you!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Awesome! Thank you! Yes, please keep coming back!

reviews.review_text: I was craving fish and chips for a week, but I refused to get it from any place other than this one. No other has compared to this one. The way they batter and fry their fish is perfection. The batter isnt too thick but still boasts such a good flavor with a perfect crisp and their fish is juicy! The portions and price are perfect as well. They take cash only, so I assume thats why there isnt a skipthedishes/ubereats/doordash option for delivery. If there were, Id be ordering here a lot more. Its a Hole-In-The-Wall/Mom-and-pops place that seems pretty off the radar. People are really really missing out.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for the awesome review! Come back for more soon!!

reviews.review_text: Fresh and flaky battered fish at extremely reasonable prices. Fries were not overly oily, but perhaps were from an older batch (as they were not super crispy). Note to owner: signage on the street lost a number - I believe it says $_.50 should you wish to make the quick fix.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your comments! Please come back soon!!

reviews.review_text: Staff are friendly, the fish b chips I ate were cooked to perfection.  Very delish and great prices
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Yes, great price indeed! Thank you

reviews.review_text: Home made style fish and chips. Simple settings, simple menu, tasty food, and friendly service. 2 slices of fish plus chips is $8.75. It keeps the same price as it opened the door over 20 years ago. Great family!  Lovely food!   Call ahead before you go. Parking: Have parking in front of the restaurant Kid-friendliness: My son loves here.  We enjoy simply conversation with the Cantonese speaking owners.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! Come back for more soon!!!

reviews.review_text: Unbeatable fish and chips! Been eating here for years and fish is always crispy on the outside, moist and juicy inside (never dry); the portion size is always super generous. Also, the aunties running the place are total sweethearts, and while its a simple little place, you can really feel the friendly and warm atmosphere. Highly recommend!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! Come back soon!

reviews.review_text: Amazing price with decent food. Fried fish is so tender. Will definitely come back again.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! Come back soon!

reviews.review_text: The halibut was tender and juicy, nice thick cut. Will definitely recommend and be back. High quality fish!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! Please come back soon for more!

reviews.review_text: Amazing fish and chips, the best in Vancouver! The service here is amazing, you are all very kind    . Great atmosphere.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. Please come back soon!

reviews.review_text: Great cheap place for fish and chips! The fish is free and the chips are crunchy and soft on the inside. The ladies who run it are super friendly. Food arrives quite fast.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Awesome, love to hear your experience. Thank you.

reviews.review_text: This is not a fancy place to sit but the two old ladies who work here are respectful. We ordered Halibut and chips and they make the food as they get the order. So, thats a nice thing and the fish too is fresh which you can see as you eat. Most Honest eatery on Kingsway!!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! Come back for more soon!

reviews.review_text: its vancouvers hidden gem!  price is good  service is good and most importantly, the food is really really good
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Wow, thank you so much for your kind words!! Come back for more soon!!

reviews.review_text: Got the dinner special. Truly good value as it comes with good clam chowder, fish was juicy and lightly battered and unsalted fries and coleslaw. Love the chowder as its not crazy salty like other places and I like how the fries are unsalted. Downside is, I wish they put in their menu specifically type of fish it was (Basa). And wish the fries were homemade. Overall, would go back again because their fish was indeed done very well and price is great value. Doesnt seem like they reuse the oil so much that makes the food taste bitter, so well done. Would go back and try the halibut instead
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much. The fries are homemade everyday right at the back of the kitchen!!

reviews.review_text: What a hidden gem! I first came here a few years ago when i was on a really tight budget. I cannot believe how high the quality of food is for the price that they charge, and it s REALLY tasty! You cannot get this quality and value anywhere! I had the honour of chatting with one of the owners.  She shared her story for why she started the restaurant and why she continues to run it. It is such a heart-warming story. I will be so sad if this place ever closes. Thank you so, so much!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the fantastic review. Much appreciated. You are right. The boss likes no fuss, no frills, just good value! Come back for more soon!

reviews.review_text: The fish and chips were absolutely perfect along with the service and atmosphere. Highly recommended
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. Please come back soon!

reviews.review_text: Nice, no frills place for reasonably priced fish and chips.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: You are right! Come back for more soon!

reviews.review_text: The batter on the fish is light and not greasy like other restaurants, and I could actually taste the fish.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: You are absolutely right! We like the batter light and crisp

reviews.review_text: Awesome family ran business, good crispy fish and prawns! Support local and come give it a try! Good prices also ! :)
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Fantastic! Please come back for more fish & prawns soon!

reviews.review_text: I and my shadow went to Sea house Fish and Chips in early May 2022 The fish is so fresh and the price is also very reasonable. This 3 pcs of big fish and homemade fried cost only $ 11.95  This price is hard to come by in this inflation situation. We plan to come monthly because we dont live in Vancouver. They accept cash only. Thats why they can offer just a low price. The point of sale systems will make the cost of food rise. I admire mother of store owner she is 90 years old and she cooks fish for us perfectly done. She is inspired me. Definitely we will be their regular customers
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! Please come once a month for our great deals!

reviews.review_text: I have driven past this place so many times and only recently brought myself to try it. Ngl it looks pretty dead from the outside but it s truly a hidden gem! It s a family owned business too. Service wasn t amazing but the taste and value makes up for it. 2 piece fish Special Value Meals $9.95 Comes with coleslaw and choice of soup or pop. The chowder surprisingly was decent with lots of clam pieces. The fish pieces were on the smaller side but the meat was juicy and the batter was thin and not too oily, very solid. Fries and coleslaw were standard. 10/10 have to get again!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Wow, thank you so much! Please come back for more soon

reviews.review_text: Great crispy battered fish. Sauces and coleslaw were really good. Service was good and the restaurant was very clean. It was empty when I attended, so I hope theyre doing good business. They deserve to make a good living. Because they are doing an excellent job.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for such a thoughtful review and your good wishes. Come back soon for more.

reviews.review_text: Been looking for a nice fish and chips joint and this one is pretty good. Nice owners, tasty food, and quiet place. Come here to eat!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Awesome and thank you!

reviews.review_text: Hidden gem. Great value and taste super good. Quiet most of the time though. Hope it stays in business as long as it can.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hey Bobby, we misssed this review. Thank you so much. 6 years later, the old lady boss is still kicking and frying. Please come back again for more!

reviews.review_text: Fish is delightfully crispy! (with both pieces devoured within 2 minutes) Although some may prefer that extra crunch, the batter is light & thumbs up for me.  The fries are decent & not as crispy, being in the supporting role, but quite filling with all that potato.  Even with the increase in price, which is very fair, solid deal on the dinner for two! (of course I was hoping for the family pack, not being too heavy on clam chowder, but the other half had eyes on that) To maintain that freshness, make sure you get home FAST! (drive or walk safely of course) We will be back, & whatever it is we order.. itll pair nicely with beers. Cheers!  #supportlocal
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! Great combo with beer!

reviews.review_text: Fish was great and the portions were good for a price of 9.99 fish and chips. Cash only. Friendly folks there.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you! Come back soon!

reviews.review_text: Good fish for really cheap.  Decor hasnt been updated in a while.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you, sir!! Come back for more soon!!

reviews.review_text: My friends and I came over for a lunch. The portions were very good. Fish was juicy and crisp on the outside (we had halibut). Nice portion of fries aa well. Good quiet environment. My friends and I enjoyed the meal.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! Please come back soon!

reviews.review_text: Food was great: Cheap, fast and filling. And Im not kidding on cheap; most affordable chip shop Ive found so far in Vancouver and Ive been around. I highly recommend this place if your ever driving by Kingsway and want something light on the wallet and filling on the stomach. Its also nice to see that the flavor hasnt changed since I was a kid and the prices are very affordable.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: This sounds awesome: light on the wallet and filling on the stomach. Thank you.

reviews.review_text: We have driven by countless times unimpressed with the outward appearance and location. But this is a lesson in don t judge with eyes alone. For a very reasonable price, you will enjoy a decent 2 piece fiah and chips without much to complain about. We were impressed that the fish was lightly battered, and not greasy or thick with dough. For this price, I was afraid that it was going to be a treasure hunt searching for the fish in the batter. In fact ours was not even  pre-battered . I saw with my eyes   four fresh fillets being coated and dropped into the fryer! The fries were good too. We forgot to grab some salt, but still good enough to munch down every crumb. There is little to be impressed by visual distractions, but I feel this is a secret for some of the best cheap eats in West Coast dinner food, and if you take a momment to chat to the owners, it is made up in delightful character.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Wow, thank you very much. Come back for more soon!

reviews.review_text: $7 1 pc fish and chips includes a drink!  3/4 size portion but is healthier anyway.  Fish moist inside, Korean crispy outside, super hot from the fryer.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! Come back soon!

reviews.review_text: Awesome fish n chips sandwiches. They make them piping hot fresh when served. The chowder is fantastic. You can also see them make your food within view. Plus a great affordable price to come back to.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you! Come back soon!

reviews.review_text: I just ordered a take out special for two. I did not expect a whole lot beforehand, but it turned out to be a nice surprise!! Especially the fish, they are perfectly fried. The batter is thin and crunchy but not hard. This is definitely a hidden gem!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you. Glad that you enjoyed it. Come back soon!

reviews.review_text: Comfort food! Very nice staff! Will definitely be back for more! I ordered the dinner for 2. The soup is absolutely amazing and if you dump the coleslaw in it, it gets even better! No time for pictures haha Fish and chips was great too. The amount of food is perfect for 2 hungry people
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Wow, never tried that before. Good idea!

reviews.review_text: Ive been eating at this place since before Google reviews and its without a doubt the best place in the lower mainland for fish and chips I still cant believe that for 20 years they have kept the quality the same delicious
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your support for so many years!! Awesome!

reviews.review_text: My family has been coming here for years, both eat in and take-out. We enjoy their fish & chip combo, its affordable and filling for the price! Their coleslaw is delicious (not overly dressed, which I prefer), but my favourite item is the clam chowder. Fragrant flavour, and I love the homemade taste with the vegetables (celery, carrots). Its more of a hole in the wall eatery but its definitely worth stopping in to check out.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Awesome. Thank you!

reviews.review_text: This is a great little mom-n-pop fish and chips eatery. The batter is very light and very crispy, which is a surprise, considering all the local fish and chips places that claim to be authentic and British, yet have soggy, oil-soaked batter. GREAT value, great service, clean restaurant, quiet atmosphere. Its a great little neighbourhood gem to support!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much. Come back soon!

reviews.review_text: The owners are really friendly, and super nice to kids. The fish is crispy and the deals are great. Its a wonderful family restaurant. 10 pieces of cod, 3 orders of chips, 2 coleslaw, and 1 gravy for only $24.10. (After tax) the coleslaw and tartar sauce are homemade, too. Cash only.
Incredible flavour. Crisp, fresh, and delicious fish and chips. Highly recommend. Try the fish burger with the bacon add-on. Lunch special like no where else in the city.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you, please come back for more soon!

reviews.review_text: They have the most juicy fish here and very good pricing! A hidden gem.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you.

reviews.review_text: Its rare to find a restaurant with good quality food at a good price. For most fish and chips place, they coat their fish with heaping amount of batter so that the customer get more flour and fish. This place do it just right: Thin coat that makes the fish crunchy but not get in the way of fish. Also we did not eat in the restaurant and have it as a takeout. The fact that the food is still nice and crunchy after the drive back gives you an idea of the quality (Ive seen many fried foods turned soggy after even a short drive) The owner is generous in servings: 10 piece cod, 2 coleslaw, 3 fries and gravy for $24!! Thats quite unheard of!! This is a mom and pop shop that I would recommend to anyone

A quaint, inconspicuous fish and chippery along Kingsway. This shop has a varied menu revolving around the British meal at incredible prices. The restaurant is owned by an Asian family (which is as authentic as it comes, as the best F&C shops in Britain are also similarly operated). The fish batter is perfectly thin and crispy and the chips are crunchy and hot - overall fantastic. The service is great and the ladies are attentive. So glad we popped in here.

The takeout family pack is INSANELY good value!  Its 10 pieces of cod, slaw, gravy, and a mound of fries and is just over $20. Highly recommend the cod.  Coating on the fish is very very crisp, and not at all bready, which I prefer over the more traditional.  This is so far my favorite fish and chip place. Staff is very nice.

You need to go there to believe it.  First impression, the place was spotless.  Not only does the owner wipe the table after each diner, she also wipes down the ketchup bottle, salt and pepper and all condiments on the table.  Wife went for the two piece fish and chips. Comes with clam chowder and cold slaw for $7.95.  Chowder is commercial chowder but thick and tasty.  Two pieces of fish done to perfection.  I had the combo with battered shrimp.  Tasty and well done.  Not your upscale fish and chip restaurant but great value for the dollar.

This place is a hidden gem, the prices were awesome, excellent value, i had the prawns and fish and chips, amazing value and so tasty prawns and fish nice and fresh, my wife had the one piece of halibut and chips $8.95 and again outstanding, we will definitely be back!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: You are right, Michell. Super Value is the core of this hidden gem. They adjusted the price once in the past 15 years in January 2022 due to pandemic rises in food costs. And I was so surprised that they only increased a dollar twenty-five here and 75 cents there! I asked the boss why not increased the price to at least match the competitors because the new prices are still 20% to 30% below market. She says, l want to make sure all our meals are affordable for the neighbours and long-term customers; I just need to break even, I dont need the extra cash!

reviews.review_text: First visit ever, Very nice people, decent food and incredible prices. Not salty food at all, especially for those sensitive to salty food.  Id never thought to go here because the place always looked closed (security bars across windows, dark inside) when in fact it was opened all the time.   Theres also a park down the road so well be stopping by with the kids this summer and taking the fish and chips down to the park for a picnic lunch in the sun. Update: tried a hamburger with cheese on a second visit. Recommend! The patty covers the entire bun, condiments all fresh. The seahouse patty isnt chewy like a McDonalds patty and a lot bigger (except quarter pounder). The seas house patty doesnt have MSG like an A&W patty (wont leave you thirsty!).  Its just a good ole homemade burger, with fries, and it came to 5.80. Cheap good and fast! (how is it possible for any restaurant to get all three?!, rules for cheap, good, fast, pick two but leave one out, but sea house has all three, cheap, good AND fast).
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Matt, Thank you so much for your comments. Come back soon!

reviews.review_text: What a wonderful discovery! This is a classic greasy spoon fish and chip spot. And I mean that in the best possible way. Spacious seating and open, fast and efficient service (I had my water glass refilled at least thrice, a rarity in Vancouver), food was prepared quickly and properly, good sized portions and all at a super reasonable price! Vancouver used to have lots of places like this ages ago but I havent been to one in about two decades. I definitely recommend if youre looking for an inexpensive meal from memory lane.
2 pc fish and chips for $7. Was very tasty, good comfort food and perfect if youre looking for a greasy, fatty meal ^-^ 10/10, will come back and recommend to my friends. Definitely fixed my craving
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Awesome! Thank you so much. Glad that you like it. Come back soon.

reviews.review_text: Great value for money! Where else can you get some tasty, crispy, fresh out of the frier fish, and fresh chips for $4.99? Amazing. They dont use cod anymore, so your choices are halibut, salmon, and fish. Probably tilapia, but its pretty good. The other standout bargain on the menu is the family pack. It has to be ordered as take out, and it comes with 10 pieces of fish, 3 orders of chips, 2 coleslaws, 2 gravies, tartar sauce, and lemon wedges--for $23 including tax. It easily feeds my family of four, and the kids love it. This place is an East Van gem, and a great place if you miss the Vancouver of yesteryear. Old school vibe, delicious, no-frills food, and the old school prices to match.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much! Our prices and menu still havent changed much. Come back soon.

I had my baby stroller with me.. and the lady was so kind to open the door for me even without me asking for help... really appreciate this :)
